## Tools Used

- Windows Update
- Windows Security dashboard
- Windows Defender Antivirus
- Windows Defender Firewall
- Microsoft Defender SmartScreen
- TPM & BitLocker
- Volume Shadow Copy Service

## Findings

- Windows Defender offers multiple scan options and maintains threat history.
- Firewall profiles protect different network contexts.
- SmartScreen and exploit protection mitigate phishing and malware risks.
- TPM and BitLocker add hardware-level encryption.
- VSS enables restore points but can be targeted by malware.

## Mitigation / Best Practices

- Keep real-time protection and controlled folder access enabled.
- Regularly update antivirus definitions and apply Windows Updates.
- Maintain firewall enabled across all profiles.
- Avoid disabling SmartScreen or exploit protection.
- Ensure TPM and BitLocker are active on supported devices.
- Maintain offline/off-site backups.


